Hydroalcoholic solutions containing 70% alcohol eliminate 99.97% (reduction of 3.5, log equivalent to a reduction of 35 decibels) of bacteria present on the hands 30 seconds after the application and 99.99% to 99.999% (reduction of 4 to 5 logs) of bacteria present on the hands 1 minute after the application.
