Less often, higher respiratory symptoms such as stretching, nasal flow or throat pain can be observed.
Gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, vomiting and diarrhea have been observed in different proportions.
Some cases in China initially showed only breast pressure and palpitations.
In some, the disease can cause pneumonia, failure of several organs and death.
